==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uplift
<hw>Up*lift"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Uplifting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To lift or raise
aloft; to raise; to elevate; <as>as, to <ex>uplift</ex> the arm; to
<ex>uplift</ex> a rock</as>.</def> <rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Satan, talking to his nearest mate,⟦br⟧
With head <qex>uplift</qex> above the wave, and eyes⟦br⟧
That sparkling blazed.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uplift</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Uplift
<hw>Up"lift`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A
raising or upheaval of strata so as to disturb their regularity and
uniformity, and to occasion folds, dislocations, and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Up-line</ent>⟦br⟧
